**Empty middleware `Name` produces an invalid pipeline directive and filter section**

The function guards against duplicate `Name` values and unknown positions, but not against an empty `Name`. A `MiddlewareSpec` with `Name == ""` and a valid position (e.g. `PipelinePositionBefore`) passes all existing guards and produces:

1. An empty token appended to `beforeFilters`, so `strings.Join` yields `" cors sizelimit service_v3"` — a pipeline directive with a leading space that PasteDeploy will fail to parse.
2. A filter section keyed `"filter:"` (empty name after the colon), which is also an invalid PasteDeploy section name.

The `pipelineValue == ""` guard at line 66 does not catch this because the joined string is non-empty (it has the space and remaining tokens).

Consider adding an early guard in the middleware-iteration loop:

```go
for _, mw := range spec.Middleware {
    if mw.Name == "" {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("pipeline %q contains a MiddlewareSpec with an empty Name", spec.PipelineName)
    }
    switch mw.Position {
    // ...
    }
}
```

